<subSubSection id="7C8E4A7F50AEB1B9A4B9263011744482" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="definition">
<paragraph id="B7A759CFCD27F7D385A1808802EE602E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Definition.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EBF6131EA03539D759E50D03F192BC46" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="0DA9177C322D10D929D1379E0F724679" authorityName="X. - X. Li &amp; Z. - Y. Qi" authorityYear="1994" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Talonostrea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Talonostrea" order="Ostreida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="20333B4A515A223345EE60B660B41B81" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Talonostrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first defined on morphological characters alone and was then monotypic, the type species 
<taxonomicName id="3522C9C53C3A0FC5364FD23A116EE565" genus="T." lsidName="T. talonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="talonata">
<emphasis id="EE684B192E271C55138A2531D44A8F3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. talonata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being described simultaneously by 
<bibRefCitation id="48498E7D3103B715610CE8C5F2DA115D" author="Li, X" journalOrPublisher="Studia Marina Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="143 - 173" refId="B19" refString="Li, X, Qi, Z, 1994. Studies on the comparative anatomy, systematic classification and evolution of Chinese oysters (In Chinese). Studia Marina Sinica 35: 143 - 173" title="Studies on the comparative anatomy, systematic classification and evolution of Chinese oysters (In Chinese)." volume="35" year="1994">Li and Qi (1994)</bibRefCitation>
. The oyster took the common name of the 
<normalizedToken id="1A6BF4BE970D569A64D9FAE10D983AF3" originalValue="‘cat’s">'cat's</normalizedToken>
paw 
<normalizedToken id="D869893DD7F62190E5E70E6E528F1181" originalValue="oyster’">oyster'</normalizedToken>
referring to the folded and broadly digitate margin of the upper valve. This contrasts with 
<taxonomicName id="5815D4CA17B446F975707215B6F0F72B" genus="T." lsidName="T. zhanjiangensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="zhanjiangensis">
<emphasis id="E0FC029CD2CE07733F29628E28A8E8FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. zhanjiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EC8AEC4771090CE0C261867528E98AA7" genus="T." lsidName="T. salpinx" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="salpinx">
<emphasis id="4A8953F9D7AE5D41D65A91D2CCF5DB55" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. salpinx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(described below), where the upper valve is flat with or without narrow fluted extensions. 
<taxonomicName id="9785E1E5D60A2E8F22D378AB5214050F" authorityName="Oliver, Salvi &amp; Al-Kandari" authorityYear="2021" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Talonostrea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Talonostrea salpinx" order="Ostreida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="salpinx">
<emphasis id="9FE5B318B155059DF3322D4F37542525" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Talonostrea salpinx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the unique feature of possessing trumpet-shaped marginal projections. The shell, therefore, offers few if any defining characters. The anatomical character of a separated style sac observed in 
<taxonomicName id="1CE8AF12B02295E6F3C4A4C2C2935EAD" genus="T." lsidName="T. talonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="talonata">
<emphasis id="9A7D9D26A2F072C4909743ED6721ECC5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. talonata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been confirmed in 
<taxonomicName id="6190BDBF51590622CB98B20A1D3E8549" genus="T." lsidName="T. zhanjiangensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="zhanjiangensis">
<emphasis id="2C128D12D6316F2EE824DFB4B70DED41" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. zhanjiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and at this time, we cannot be sure if this character is an apomorphy of 
<taxonomicName id="BF98147E176E3688907D26CB19D33771" genus="T." lsidName="T. talonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="talonata">
<emphasis id="D4BD666DB62074F7E64E043DD3099A5F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. talonata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a synapomorphy of the genus as a whole. The anatomical arrangement in 
<taxonomicName id="A39C979B7FE58A0E67CC6105882C4CC4" genus="T." lsidName="T. salpinx" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="salpinx">
<emphasis id="21EC55431AF0024C578472358F3E11AD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. salpinx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) agrees with that of 
<taxonomicName id="F2FDDF32AD16E403FE6D742AD46EEB3A" genus="T." lsidName="T. talonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="talonata">
<emphasis id="D66BA2F5C6CF6ACF4E52AFD01FFA5888" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. talonata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="3B620012B3B6A6084283D64732A66729" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jembe.2018.11.011" author="Cavaleiro, NP" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Experimental Marine Biology and Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="91 - 99" refId="B8" refString="Cavaleiro, NP, Lazoski, C, Tureck, CR, Melo, CMR, do Amaral, VS, Lomovasky, BJ, Absher, TM, Sole-Cava, AM, 2019. Crassostrea talonata, a new threat to native oyster (Bivalvia: Ostreidae) culture in the Southwest Atlantic. Journal of Experimental Marine Biology and Ecology 511: 91 - 99, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jembe.2018.11.011" title="Crassostrea talonata, a new threat to native oyster (Bivalvia: Ostreidae) culture in the Southwest Atlantic." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jembe.2018.11.011" volume="511" year="2019">Cavaleiro et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
and therefore does suggest that this is a defining feature of 
<taxonomicName id="FAA24C2DA709CCC227B35C3CB7B955A2" authorityName="X. - X. Li &amp; Z. - Y. Qi" authorityYear="1994" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Talonostrea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Talonostrea" order="Ostreida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BB1E224DDC4819BFAA336BD58C392971" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Talonostrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As the anatomy of 
<taxonomicName id="A9ACB7004CB88146E446738364E19DF4" genus="T." lsidName="T. zhanjiangensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="zhanjiangensis">
<emphasis id="1A54C331B23D9ACA6941A45167B680A9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. zhanjiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been described, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="CDD9A77D17B61CF89C806354429A5B88" authorityName="X. - X. Li &amp; Z. - Y. Qi" authorityYear="1994" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Talonostrea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Talonostrea" order="Ostreida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0299CCCD97167A0C63A559DAD995813" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Talonostrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed on molecular data alone (
<bibRefCitation id="320FE516BC8BB9770D9D7D804E0E790B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12455" author="Salvi, D" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="263 - 276" refId="B29" refString="Salvi, D, Mariottini, P, 2017. Molecular taxonomy in 2D: A novel ITS2 rRNA sequence-structure approach guides the description of the oysters' subfamily Saccostreinae and the genus Magallana (Bivalvia: Ostreidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 179: 263 - 276, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12455" title="Molecular taxonomy in 2 D: A novel ITS 2 rRNA sequence-structure approach guides the description of the oysters' subfamily Saccostreinae and the genus Magallana (Bivalvia: Ostreidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12455" volume="179" year="2017">Salvi and Mariottini 2017</bibRefCitation>
) but it is possible that the separate style sac/mid gut character will prove to be a synapomorphy of the genus.
</paragraph>
